1
00:00:03,235 --> 00:00:05,503
Hey, Mind Field! Vanessa here.

2
00:00:05,504 --> 00:00:09,107
Just kidding. My name
is actually Michael.

3
00:00:09,108 --> 00:00:11,676
That part when I said
that I was Vanessa...

4
00:00:11,677 --> 00:00:13,611
that was a lie.

5
00:00:13,612 --> 00:00:15,547
So you're welcome.

6
00:00:15,548 --> 00:00:18,149
Humans love lies.

7
00:00:18,150 --> 00:00:19,517
More precisely,

8
00:00:19,518 --> 00:00:22,320
we love things
that aren't entirely true--

9
00:00:22,321 --> 00:00:23,788
because we have to.

10
00:00:23,789 --> 00:00:25,690
It's often all we have.

11
00:00:25,691 --> 00:00:28,193
Completely proving something
can be difficult,

12
00:00:28,194 --> 00:00:30,361
if not impossible.

13
00:00:30,362 --> 00:00:33,698
So instead, we have
the faith of the believer,

14
00:00:33,699 --> 00:00:36,668
the confidence interval
of the scientist.

15
00:00:36,669 --> 00:00:38,770
What we think we know,

16
00:00:38,771 --> 00:00:42,207
we really only believe we know.

17
00:00:42,208 --> 00:00:44,809
On this episode of Mind Field, 
I'm going to take a look at

18
00:00:44,810 --> 00:00:47,745
a kind of lie
we tell ourselves.

19
00:00:47,746 --> 00:00:55,587
And I'm going to use belief
to turn a lie...into a truth.

20
00:00:55,588 --> 00:01:09,434
 ( theme music playing )

21
00:01:09,435 --> 00:01:12,203
